**Exploring quote escaping in Node**

I'm trying to figure out why quotes are escaped with backslashes when using Node spawn with arguments that contain spaces. It seems that CreateProcess adds backslashes to the quotes in the argument because cmd receives them literally. I think it's due to passing the /c line with quotes, which causes Node to escape the inner quotes. Maybe if I set `windowsVerbatimArguments: true`, it won't escape them. I should definitely test this out.
